title: For Sale:  Scarce Matching German Borsigwalde K98k S/243 1938
postcontent: Scarce, matching pre-war K98k Mauser...this S/243-code rifle was manufactured by veteran producer Mauser Borsigwalde under contract with the Third Reich in the year preceding the outbreak of WWII. A correct example, the rifle has standard features correct for the time and producer, including numerous, unmarred Eagle/Swaztika acceptance marks/Waffenamts(WaA280), laminated Beechwood furniture with flat buttplate, no sight hood, and all-matching numbers. A long-serving veteran of the war, owing to the rifle's early production time frame, it also notably feature two Weimar droop-eagle proofs on the barrel and receiver. Lacking an import mark, this K98k is a strong candidate for having been brought back from the war as a GI's trophy. With such examples rapidly becoming scarce on the market, this desirable, pre-war 98k represents a sound investment and would be a superb addition to the advanced or dedicated collection.
